Heres how you can do it in TypeScript:

1. Create a type for your expected body shape:
```ts
interface LoginBody {
  username: string;
  password: string;
}
```

2. In your route handler, use a type assertion:
```ts
app.use(koaBody());

router.post('/login', async (ctx: Context) => {
  const { username, password } = ctx.request.body as LoginBody;
  // ...rest of your code
});
```

3. (Optional, for global type safety) You can extend Koas types globally:
```ts
// types/koa.d.ts
import 'koa';

declare module 'koa' {
  interface Request {
    body: any; // or a more specific type if you want
  }
}
```
Then, make sure this file is included in your `tsconfig.json`.

